  </div>
</div>
Toast Usage Examples:

After Saving:

"Erfolgreich gespeichert!" (Success)
"Die Daten wurden erfolgreich gespeichert."
After Deleting:

"Erfolgreich gelöscht!" (Success)
"Der Eintrag wurde entfernt."
After Updating:

"Änderungen gespeichert!" (Success)
"Ihre Änderungen wurden übernommen."
On Error:

"Fehler beim Speichern" (Error)
"Bitte überprüfen Sie Ihre Eingaben."
On Warning:

"Unvollständige Eingabe" (Warning)
"Bitte füllen Sie alle Pflichtfelder aus."
Interaction States:

Modal entrance: Fade in with scale animation (animate-in)
Modal exit: Fade out with scale animation
Backdrop click: Close modal (optional, based on context)
ESC key: Close modal
Tab switching: Smooth content transition
Form validation: Show error states with red borders and error messages
Accessibility Requirements:

Focus trap: Keep focus within modal when open
ARIA labels: role="dialog", aria-modal="true", aria-labelledby
Toast ARIA: role="alert" for important messages, role="status" for info
Keyboard navigation: Tab through all interactive elements
Close button: Always accessible and visible
Focus visible states: Clear outline on focused elements
Screen reader announcements: Toast messages should be announced
Responsive Behavior:

Mobile: Full-screen or nearly full-screen (mx-4 for small margins)
Tablet/Desktop: Centered with max-width constraint
Max height: max-h-[90vh] with overflow-y-auto for scrollable content
Padding adjustments: Reduce padding on smaller screens
Toast positioning: Adjust to top-center on mobile if needed
Key Requirements:

Always use dark blue gradient backgrounds for modals
Maintain yellow/gold accent color (#F5B800) for active states
Show toast notification after every significant action (save, delete, update)
Use appropriate toast type (success, error, warning, info)
Auto-dismiss toasts after appropriate duration
Stack multiple toasts vertically if needed
Ensure proper contrast ratios for accessibility (WCAG AA minimum)
Use smooth transitions for all state changes
Include proper focus management and keyboard support
Form fields should have clear labels and validation states
Close button always visible and accessible

bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-[#f7f2eb]/30 rounded-xl p-3 shadow-lg border border-[#d4af37]/10



**Filter Panel Container:**
bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-[#f7f2eb]/20 rounded-xl p-4 shadow-lg border border-[#d4af37]/30



**Card Container:**
p-3 bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-[#f7f2eb]/50 rounded-xl hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-[#d4af37]/10 transition-all duration-300 border border-[#d4af37]/10 hover:border-[#d4af37]/40 hover:scale-[1.02] active:scale-[0.98]



**Header Container:**
flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-start lg:items-center justify-between gap-2 mb-2



### Responsive Patterns
**Text Visibility:**
- Hide text on mobile, show on desktop: `<span className="hidden sm:inline">Text</span>`
- Show abbreviated on mobile: `<span className="sm:hidden">Short</span>`

**Button Text:**
```jsx
<span className="hidden sm:inline">Full Text</span>
<span className="sm:hidden">Short</span>
Layout Adjustments:

Mobile: flex-col
Desktop: lg:flex-row
Items alignment: items-start lg:items-center
Standard Color Palette
Primary Colors:

Gold Primary: #d4af37
Gold Secondary: #c19a2e
Text Colors:

Primary: #0a253c
Secondary: #666666
Tertiary: #999999
White: text-white
Background Colors:

Light Background: #f7f2eb
White: bg-white
Gradient Light: from-white to-[#f7f2eb]/30
Status Colors:

Success: bg-green-100 text-green-700
Error: bg-red-100 text-red-700
Warning: bg-orange-100 text-orange-700
Info: bg-blue-100 text-blue-700
Accessibility Requirements
Minimum Touch Targets:

Buttons: min-h-[40px] for mobile
Inputs: min-h-[44px] for easy interaction
Focus States:

Always include: focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#d4af37]/50
Outline removal: outline-none (only when ring is present)
Keyboard Navigation:

All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
Focus trap in modals
Clear focus indicators
Animation Classes
Slide Down:


animate-slideDown
Fade In:


animate-in
Scale Transitions:

Hover: hover:scale-105 or hover:scale-[1.02]
Active: active:scale-95 or active:scale-[0.98]
Usage Guidelines
When creating new components, always:

Use these standardized sizes for consistency
Apply the same color palette and opacity levels
Include proper hover and active states
Add smooth transitions
Ensure minimum touch target sizes
Include accessibility features (focus rings, ARIA labels)
Test responsive behavior on mobile and desktop